      "writtenOn": "2018-05-01T18:22:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we should change this timeout. \n\nDue to the way GAE works, flushes are handled synchronously with handling user requests: whenever we flush, we block some (random) user request until the flush completes. \n\nI believe faulty monitoring must not degrade the performance (99% response time percentile in this case, but still...) of the service being monitoring. Thus I think we should not increase this deadline. A slow flush \u003d\u003d\u003d failed flush.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 242,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 242,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "8af19840c928cf64b2355a1adb50175ca7af5413",
