      "writtenOn": "2018-05-01T18:22:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Strictly speaking, bad things will start to happen if we don\u0027t call TaskNumAllocator.NotifyTaskIsAlive frequently enough (at least once in 30 min, see https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/appengine/tsmon/tasknum.go?q\u003dTaskNumAllocator.NotifyTaskIsAlive\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026l\u003d141).\n\nIf we care about extended tsmon outages, it might be necessary to refactor the flush to ping NotifyTaskIsAlive independently of flushing to tsmon (note that TaskNumAllocator thingy is completely independent of tsmon and fails at a different time (if datastore is down)).\n\nThis can be done in a separate CL though (if at all).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 271,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 271,
        "endChar": 21
      },
